my time can be bought for a mere 10 or 100pp?<br><br>If I want a tp, ress, sow, buff, summoned item, or whatever from someone I ask politely and almost always get a polite response in return. If it's a yes I say thank you and move on to whereever I am heading, and if it's a no I say have a nice day and move on to ask someone else. Simple as that.<br><br>How does it works for you guys? <p>Love, Edeina<br>Highelf Conjurer of Erollisi<br>Ayonae Ro Server<br><a href="http://Ayonae.Ro">Ayonae.Ro</a> Server Community Board</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/usirtaino.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SirTainO</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elite Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/8/01 4:29:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=221.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.jollyjokers.com/images/pally.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Always pay for TP and ress?</span><hr size=1> I tell ya something really simple.<br><br>Looking for a TP to DL.<br>---------<br><br>Looking for a TP to DL. Donating 50pp.<br>--- I will take you<br>--- I can give ya lift<br>--- On my way...<br><br><br>Looking for a rezz for a friend.<br>---------<br><br>Looking for a rezz for a friend, donating.<br>- Where are you? Ahh thats too far.<br><br>Looking for a rezz for a friend, paying 100pp.<br>- Bring the body, I wil see whether I find some time.<br><br>Looking for a rezz for a friend, donating 200pp.<br>- Ok comming<br><br><br>I must have spent around 5k for TPs and the same amount of money for Rezzes so far.<br><br>I never got money for any favor and I would never expect or accept any for buffs or heals or whatever. Or Revives. <br><br>Lately a guildie reported that he saw someone offering SENSE HEADING for donations. <br><br><br>This is how Norrath works, hun.<br> <p><center><a href="mailto:taino@jollyjokers.com"><img src="http://www.jollyjokers.com/images/sign.jpg"></a><br><font face="Arial"><font size=2><b><a href="http://pub52.ezboard.com/bjollyjokersfoundation">~ Legend of the Jokers ~</a>  <br>- JoKeR by Heart & Soul -<a href="http://www.jollyjokers.com">Jolly~JoKeRs</a></FONT></center></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/usirtaino.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SirTainO</A> at: 5/8/01 4:31:50 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uedeina.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Edeina</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Board Mistress</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/8/01 4:50:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=221.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Always pay for TP and ress?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br><br>This is how Norrath works, hun.<br><br><hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>Your Norrath, not mine.<br>And my world is true as well - I have played since beta.<br><br>This is *not* about Edeina being a babe and Taino being male. My cleric is male, and he lives in the same world as my magician. Granted, he's a cleric. But he can only revive and not give xp back, so people have no reason to suck up to him. Certainly, people are statistically slightly nicer to female chars, but I don't notice all that much of a difference between my two post level 30 chars.<br><br>Perhaps it comes down to the basic fact that you get what you ask for. If you auction for help then only the people who want your money will reply. I don't think I have *ever* shouted for a TP, and extremely rarely for a ress. Much less auctioned.<br><br>The &quot;sense heading for donation&quot; thing do sound like a good joke btw. Something I could have created a newbie to do <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Love, Edeina<br>Highelf Conjurer of Erollisi<br>Ayonae Ro Server<br><a href="http://Ayonae.Ro">Ayonae.Ro</a> Server Community Board</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ucrydeeossiriand.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Crydee Ossiriand</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elder</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/8/01 5:11:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=221.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Always pay for TP and ress?</span><hr size=1> I find that Teleports are rarely free unless it is someone picking me up for a raid, the porter is a personal friend, or the group decided to relocate to some place that porting would be the fastest way to get there.<br><br>Most rezes I got have been free and this includes rezes I had to get for other people. *hugs the clerics*<br><br><br>I've been told that I am too nice to everyone - I never charge for buffs, I'll track for free, and will make any trade skill produced item at the cost of materials.<br> <p><P><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE="2"><B>Crydee Ossiriand</B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE="1">The Questing Ranger on Ayonae Ro<BR><A HREF="http://monsterweb.org">http://monsterweb.org</A><BR><BR>Person looking at my inventory... What quest loot do you drop?</FONT></P></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/usilencce.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Silencce</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Regular Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/8/01 5:20:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=221.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Always pay for TP and ress?</span><hr size=1> i find that what taino said is mostly true, if you want immidate action, offer up the dough, and i help others with this, exp: in Lguk somone at the zone shouts &quot;looking for a rezz for 2 people will give all i have 50pp...&quot; and i notice they are shouting for some time... ill usually shout out &quot;adding 100pp more to that 50 and giving clarity to the cleric who can rezz&quot; and this produces results. why would you do this to random people do you ask? A) not all are as lucky as i have been, B) thats sure as hell how i'd like to be treated, C) Everyone, and i mean everyone, does whats in their best intrest, rational self intrest, i do that because there is something in it for me, otherwise i wouldnt do it. Whats in it for me? A) the hopes that one day when im in the gutter somewhere under some ogre( no offense ogre's) that i'll be returned a favor, B) it makes me feel better about myself, call me a jackass but you know its the truth about any nice thing you might do, in the end you feel better because yo helped someone who was in need. i wish this was the case in RL sometimes but i cant exactly go giving 100 bucks to some random guy on the street, i wish i could, but i cant yet being in school still :-) lol.<br><br>I also think there is another reason that i would offer money for a rezz that i wasnt associated with at all or knew the person from any time before. But i think that if one person starts it in the zone, maybe, just maybe it will wear off a little on others and they'll help someone else out in the future, even if its not myself...<br><br><br>(ok i have a problem with run-on's, so shoot me but at least i know i have the problem lol <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  hehehe) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uledge.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ledge</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Regular Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/8/01 6:18:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=221.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Always pay for TP and ress?</span><hr size=1> I almost never have time to port total strangers around. I will make time to port someone for 200pp or more. <br><br>The way i look at it is, these people have the money, 200pp is nothing in the grand scheme of things to them, and they don't want to wait around to find someone for 10-15pp.<br><br>They are paying not so much for my time, but to save theirs. <br><br>I will always port guildies and allies for free. I will port peeps for free if I have down time (rare nowadays). I will buff sow, regen thorns free pretty much whenever I'm asked.<br><br>I don't think people should pay me for ports, but I also feel they should not expect me to do it for free. <br><br>Thunderpaw <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ucraeven.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Craeven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Regular Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/8/01 6:40:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=221.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Always pay for TP and ress?</span><hr size=1> Well back in the old days when I had my cleric if someone would say, &quot;I'll pay 50pp for a res, it's all I have&quot; I'd usually do it for free. Mostly I just took whatever was offered tho.  For now I have my personal clerics with thier sticks (*waves to Shallondra and Scyy*) so getting a res is really no big deal to me.<br><br>As for TPs.. usually if I'm asking for a TP I'm traveling pretty far and need to get there quick.  I'm a big tipper too.. I usually give 100pp for a TP and I get FAST results and generally don't have to wait for them to fill up a full TP group.  I figure it's worth the money to get a TP from FV to Iceclad since it would take a couple hours by boat.<br><br>Astonyx - 60 Oracle - Undead Lords <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ujableakl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>jableakl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardfellow</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/8/01 6:42:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=221.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Always pay for TP and ress?</span><hr size=1> This is a Lassie Faire society. Meaning it is a free market that has no controling hand defining price. Therefore it is what the buyer and the seller will agree to. This basic Economics 101. There is no guideline to determine what you should pay, how you should pay etc... it is just a matter of what the TP/Res or whatever is worth to you and how much you can afford. Therefore the buy determines what their time is worth and is willing to pay for it and the seller determines what they are willing to perform their service for. Where these meet equals a market. <p>Cuthbert Dirgewielder <BR>El Virtuoso and Uber Geek of F.U.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uconaddor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Conaddor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/8/01 7:15:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=221.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Always pay for TP and ress?</span><hr size=1> Well for me it has mostly been pay as I go.<br><br>If I need a gate I will always /shout Paying 50pp for Gate / Tele to &lt;insert Destination here&gt; please ).  I usually get a ride within 5 mins.  If I am in a big hurry I up it to 100pp and will get a ride quick.  Sometimes one of my friends will here me shouting for a ride and will come to my aid free of charge.  I feel that I won't ask friends to use thier game time to gate me around when I have pp to do it myself.  If they offer I am grateful.  Sometimes folks will gate me and tell me that they only want xpp because that is what they feel it is worth, even other times they will say free)<br><br>I have only paid for a res a few times.  On at least one occation I had to offer 500pp to get a res.  Compared to the exp loss I will pay it.  I always will buff people for free.  I would not ask a cleric to leave a camp to come res me for free.  If I can avoid it in non guild raids / groups I won't even ask the guild I will get one arranged on site.  I feel it isn't fair to put your friends thru hoops because I made a boo boo.<br><br>Melee people feel this much more than the casting/priest classes.  ( We can't bind around the corner )<br><br> <p>Conaddor Trueheart<BR>59th Ranger of Surefall Glade<BR>The Looking Glass<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ufridolinpopelbart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fridolin Popelbart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>New to the block</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/8/01 8:20:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=221.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Always pay for TP and ress?</span><hr size=1> Tell you what, play a cleric 39+ non-anon.<br>IF I do that ( mostly only when LFG in KC or OS ) my text screen goes like this :<br><br>Rez_beggar : Could you rez me ? I died in ...<br>Rez_beggar01 : Hey bro, I need a rez, plz come and rez me.<br>Rez_beggar02 : Could you rez me ? I died in ...<br>Rez_beggar03 : Hey bro, I need a rez, plz come and rez me.<br>Rez_beggar04 : Could you rez me ? I died in ...<br>Rez_beggar05 : Hey bro, I need a rez, plz come and rez me.<br><br>I am not talking about the rez noodle here, mind you.<br>I would not take cash for doing two clicks only.<br><br>But if I cross a zone , spend an assload of mana and then have to med 5 minutes to get the mana back I expect more than a warm handshake.<br><br>If you get rezzed, you take, depending on the distance I have to cross, anything from 7-8min to 30min of my time.<br>Playing time I could spend with friends, mastering a tradeskill, hunting for XP, cash or items.<br>Additionally, I save you time. But the time saved here goes anywhere from an hour to days or weeks of YOUR time, considering that some people level very slowly or would be unable to reach the place with the corpse without help.<br><br>And now tell me, a rez of the 49er or 56er Caliber is not worth some of your cash ?<br>Sory, but in what kind of world do you live ?? <br>Why could ANYONE think or EXPECT a stranger to help you just for a thank you ?<br><br>*Takes a deep breath*<br>And please spare me those Christian teachings outta the bible. They arent how the world works. And I really would prefer not to involve them here .  Of course I know that its exactly what would happen, someone saying its a good and friendly action to help like a samarite.<br>Sorry bro, I don't believe in your god and my religion has a whole set of different teachings.<br>So spare me the christian teachings please.<br>*Releases the air*<br><br>You want me to invest my time to save yours, then invest.<br>Be it buffs, cash, items or help.<br>But not just a warm handshake, I can get those for free too. Without having to sit down and do diddly for 5 minutes after.<br><br><br>Frid<br>A Cleric<br>/roleplay on 99% <p><font size="4" style="courier"><b>Fridolin Popelbart</font><font size="3"><BR>Level 51 Cleric</b><a href="http://www.storm-of-eternity.de"><font size="4"><BR><i>Storm of Eternity</a></i><BR><font size="3"><BR><i>Avandol "Green Toes" Sulrissil</i><BR>A_true_Paladin_00</font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ushallondra.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shallondra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Regular Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/8/01 10:04:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=221.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Always pay for TP and ress?</span><hr size=1> /wave Astonyx. ;><br><br>Why take offense when someone offers pp for a port?  I do it all the time, when I'm /shouting for a port.  I consider it my duty to thank someone for the time they took out for the port.  I never directly ask someone in a tell for a port, it's always a random shout and whomever wishes to respond, does and I always appreciate it.  I show that with the offer to pay for their services.  Sometimes I'm refused, sometimes it's accepted, it's the way of it.<br><br>As far as res's go, I never solicite money.  If it's offered, I sometimes take it, especially if I went out of my way to get to the corpse. 